@jasonpet @abaruni @csantanapr 
Could you please also have a look, to not delete valid documents in the trigger databases?
Thanks a lot in advance :)

@rabbah 
* There is no need to exclude this test in Travis because it only tries to *create* the action. It does *not execute* it. So the test is probably much faster than most of the other action limit tests.
 * You are right, there already is a [timeout action](https://github.com/apache/incubator-openwhisk/blob/master/tests/dat/actions/timeout.js). This timeout action uses a busy wait loop and thus, uses much more CPU than a timeout should use. My plan is to replace the existing timeout action with my new lean timeout action in a following PR once this PR is merged.

Thanks for this patch. The culprit is `waitOnMetadata` in the `send` method
```
            ClusterAndWaitTime clusterAndWaitTime = waitOnMetadata(record.topic(), record.partition(), maxBlockTimeMs);
```

I generally agree then with the fix. Since now the code would use a Scala future, we can eliminate the callback passed to the Java future and just use `andThen`.

@markusthoemmes @cbickel one of you please also have a look.
